    "asOf": "2021-06-28",
    "date": "2023-08-04T20:52:45Z",
    "text": "Strengthening Social Security for Survivors Act\n\nThis bill allows eligible widows, widowers, surviving former spouses, parents, and children of a deceased worker to claim Social Security survivor benefits retroactive to the date of the worker's death.\n\nCurrent law limits retroactive claims for survivors benefits to six months."
